<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="WKSP-020" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create WorkspaceLayoutService — Dataverse CRUD for sprk_workspacelayout</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>bff-api</tags>
    <estimated-effort>6h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation — creates a new service class with Dataverse WebApi CRUD operations, OBO auth, business rule enforcement (max 10, single default); ADR-001 and ADR-010 constraints apply</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>003, 004</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <role>Senior .NET developer implementing workspace layout API</role>
    <goal>
      Create a WorkspaceLayoutService class that handles all Dataverse CRUD operations for the
      sprk_workspacelayout entity via OBO-authenticated Dataverse WebApi calls. This service is
      the single backend component for reading, creating, updating, and deleting user workspace
      layouts. System layouts (e.g., "Corporate Workspace") are defined as code constants and
      returned alongside user layouts — they are never stored in Dataverse.
    </goal>
    <context>
      The BFF API uses .NET 8 Minimal API with OBO (On-Behalf-Of) authentication to call the
      Dataverse WebApi. Existing services like SpeFileStore demonstrate the pattern for making
      authenticated Dataverse calls. The sprk_workspacelayout entity stores per-user layout
      configurations with fields: sprk_workspacelayoutid (GUID PK), sprk_name, sprk_templateid,
      sprk_sectionsjson (JSON blob with schemaVersion), sprk_isdefault (boolean), sprk_sortorder
      (int), and standard owner fields. Task 003 defines the entity schema and Task 004 defines
      the DTO types (WorkspaceLayoutDto, CreateWorkspaceLayoutRequest, UpdateWorkspaceLayoutRequest).
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST use Minimal API patterns — no MVC controllers (ADR-001)
      - MUST register as concrete type, not interface, unless a seam is required (ADR-010)
      - MUST enforce max 10 user layouts per user on create — return 409 Conflict if exceeded
      - MUST enforce single default — when setting a layout as default, clear isDefault on all other user layouts
      - MUST NOT store system layouts in Dataverse — define as code constants
      - MUST return system layouts alongside user layouts in list operations
      - MUST use OBO-authenticated Dataverse WebApi calls
      - MUST return ProblemDetails-compatible error information for service-level failures
      - MUST filter Dataverse queries by ownerid to ensure user isolation
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/service-registration.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>Dataverse WebApi CRUD: use HttpClient with OBO token to call /api/data/v9.2/sprk_workspacelayouts</pattern>
      <pattern>OBO auth: acquire token via ITokenAcquisition for Dataverse scope, pass as Bearer header</pattern>
      <pattern>System layouts: define as static readonly WorkspaceLayoutDto constants, merge into list results</pattern>
      <pattern>Max 10 enforcement: query count of user layouts before insert, reject with 409 if >= 10</pattern>
      <pattern>Single default: on create/update with isDefault=true, issue PATCH to clear isDefault on all other user layouts first</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/ (new WorkspaceLayoutService.cs)</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/SpeFileStore.cs (pattern reference)</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/ (DTO types from Task 004)</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read the existing service pattern in SpeFileStore.cs and the BFF API CLAUDE.md to understand DI registration, authentication, and Dataverse WebApi call patterns</step>
    <step order="2">Read the DTO types created in Task 004 (WorkspaceLayoutDto, CreateWorkspaceLayoutRequest, UpdateWorkspaceLayoutRequest) to understand the data contracts</step>
    <step order="3">Define system layout constants — create a static class or static field holding the "Corporate Workspace" system layout as a WorkspaceLayoutDto with a well-known GUID, marked as system (isSystem=true)</step>
    <step order="4">Implement GetLayoutsAsync — query Dataverse for user layouts filtered by ownerid, prepend system layout constants, return combined list sorted by system-first then sortOrder</step>
    <step order="5">Implement GetLayoutByIdAsync — check system layout constants first (return immediately if match), otherwise query Dataverse by ID with ownerid filter</step>
    <step order="6">Implement GetDefaultLayoutAsync — query Dataverse for the user layout with sprk_isdefault=true; if none found, return the system default layout constant</step>
    <step order="7">Implement CreateLayoutAsync — count existing user layouts (enforce max 10, return error if exceeded), handle isDefault toggle (clear others if setting as default), POST to Dataverse WebApi, return created layout</step>
    <step order="8">Implement UpdateLayoutAsync — verify layout exists and is not a system layout, handle isDefault toggle, PATCH to Dataverse WebApi, return updated layout</step>
    <step order="9">Implement DeleteLayoutAsync — verify layout exists and is not a system layout, DELETE via Dataverse WebApi; if deleted layout was default, do not auto-assign a new default</step>
    <step order="10">Run dotnet build to verify compilation succeeds with no errors</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 020 status from pending to completed</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/WorkspaceLayoutService.cs — Dataverse CRUD service</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Workspace/SystemWorkspaceLayouts.cs — static system layout definitions</artifact>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">WorkspaceLayoutService compiles and exposes GetLayoutsAsync, GetLayoutByIdAsync, GetDefaultLayoutAsync, CreateLayoutAsync, UpdateLayoutAsync, and DeleteLayoutAsync methods</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">GetLayoutsAsync returns system layouts prepended to user layouts, filtered by the calling user's ownerid</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">CreateLayoutAsync returns a 409-equivalent error when the user already has 10 layouts</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Setting isDefault=true on create or update clears isDefault on all other user layouts before applying</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">System layouts are defined as code constants and are never written to or read from Dataverse</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">dotnet build passes with no errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>Phase 3 Group B — depends on 003 (entity schema) and 004 (DTO types). Safe to run in parallel with other Group B tasks. Tasks 021 and 022 depend on this task. Own files: WorkspaceLayoutService.cs (new), SystemWorkspaceLayouts.cs (new).</protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
